<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Joshua 12:1-24</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="24">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="24">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now these are the kings of the land whom the sons of Israel defeated and whose land they then took possession of on the side of the Jordan toward the rising of the sun, from the torrent valley of Ar&acute;non up to Mount Her&acute;mon and all the Ar&acute;a&middot;bah toward the sunrise:</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Si&acute;hon the king of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites, who dwelt in Hesh&acute;bon, ruling from A&middot;ro&acute;er, which was on the bank of the torrent valley of Ar&acute;non, and the middle of the torrent valley, and half of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad as far as Jab&acute;bok the torrent valley, the boundary of the sons of Am&acute;mon,</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">and the Ar&acute;a&middot;bah as far as the sea of Chin&acute;ne&middot;reth toward the east and as far as the sea of the Ar&acute;a&middot;bah, the Salt Sea, to the east in the direction of Beth-jesh&acute;i&middot;moth, and toward the south under the slopes of Pis&acute;gah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And the territory of Og the king of Ba&acute;shan, of what was left over of the Reph&acute;a&middot;im, who dwelt in Ash&acute;ta&middot;roth and Ed&acute;re&middot;i,</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">and who ruled in Mount Her&acute;mon and in Sal&acute;e&middot;cah and in all Ba&acute;shan, as far as the boundary of the Gesh&acute;ur&middot;ites and the Ma&middot;ac&acute;a&middot;thites, and half of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad, to the territory of Si&acute;hon the king of Hesh&acute;bon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">It was Moses the servant of Jehovah and the sons of Israel who defeated them, after which Moses the servant of Jehovah gave it as a holding to the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ites and the Gad&acute;ites and half of the tribe of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And these are the kings of the land whom Joshua and the sons of Israel defeated on the side of the Jordan toward the west, from Ba&acute;al-gad in the valley plain of Leb&acute;a&middot;non and as far as Mount Ha&acute;lak, which goes up to Se&acute;ir, after which Joshua gave it to the tribes of Israel as a holding by their shares,</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">in the mountainous region and in the She&middot;phe&acute;lah and in the Ar&acute;a&middot;bah and on the slopes and in the wilderness and in the Neg&acute;eb—the Hit&acute;tites, the Am&acute;or&middot;ites and the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ites, the Per&acute;iz&middot;zites, the Hi&acute;vites and the Jeb&acute;u&middot;sites:</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">The king of Jer&acute;i&middot;cho, one; the king of A&acute;i, which was beside Beth&acute;el, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">the king of Jerusalem, one; the king of He&acute;bron, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">the king of Jar&acute;muth, one; the king of La&acute;chish, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">the king of Eg&acute;lon, one; the king of Ge&acute;zer, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">the king of De&acute;bir, one; the king of Ge&acute;der, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">the king of Hor&acute;mah, one; the king of A&acute;rad, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">the king of Lib&acute;nah, one; the king of A&middot;dul&acute;lam, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">the king of Mak&middot;ke&acute;dah, one; the king of Beth&acute;el, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">the king of Tap&acute;pu&middot;ah, one; the king of He&acute;pher, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">the king of A&acute;phek, one; the king of Las&middot;shar&acute;on, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">the king of Ma&acute;don, one; the king of Ha&acute;zor, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">the king of Shim&acute;ron-me&acute;ron, one; the king of Ach&acute;shaph, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">the king of Ta&acute;a&middot;nach, one; the king of Me&middot;gid&acute;do, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">the king of Ke&acute;desh, one; the king of Jok&acute;ne&middot;am in Car&acute;mel, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">the king of Dor on the mountain ridge of Dor, one; the king of Goi&acute;im in Gil&acute;gal, one;</span>
</p>

<p class="z"><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">the king of Tir&acute;zah, one;<br>all the kings being thirty-one.</span>
</p>
</form>

