<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Joshua 16:1-10</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="24">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="10">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And the lot came out for the sons of Joseph from the Jordan at Jer&acute;i&middot;cho to the waters of Jer&acute;i&middot;cho eastward, the wilderness going up from Jer&acute;i&middot;cho into the mountainous region of Beth&acute;el.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And it went out from Beth&acute;el belonging to Luz and passed over to the boundary of the Ar&acute;chites at At&acute;a&middot;roth,</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">and it went down westward to the boundary of the Japh&acute;le&middot;tites as far as the boundary of Lower Beth-ho&acute;ron and Ge&acute;zer, and its termination proved to be at the sea.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And the sons of Joseph, Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh and E&acute;phra&middot;im, proceeded to take possession of land.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And the boundary of the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im by their families came to be, yes, the boundary of their inheritance toward the east came to be At&acute;a&middot;roth-ad&acute;dar, as far as Upper Beth-ho&acute;ron;</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">and the boundary went out to the sea. Mich&middot;me&acute;thath was on the north, and the boundary went around eastward to Ta&acute;a&middot;nath-shi&acute;loh, and passed over eastward to Ja&middot;no&acute;ah.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And it went down from Ja&middot;no&acute;ah to At&acute;a&middot;roth and Na&acute;a&middot;rah and reached to Jer&acute;i&middot;cho and went out to the Jordan.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">From Tap&acute;pu&middot;ah the boundary moved on westward to the torrent valley of Ka&acute;nah, and its termination proved to be at the sea. This is the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im by their families.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im had enclave cities in the midst of the inheritance of the sons of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh, all the cities and their settlements.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And they did not drive away the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ites who were dwelling in Ge&acute;zer, and the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ites continue dwelling in among E&acute;phra&middot;im down to this day and came to be subject to slavish forced labor.</span>
</p>
</form>

