<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Joshua 19:1-51</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="24">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="51">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Then the second lot came out for Sim&acute;e&middot;on, for the tribe of the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on by their families. And their inheritance came to be in the midst of the inheritance of the sons of Judah.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And they came to have in their inheritance Be&acute;er-she&acute;ba with She&acute;ba, and Mo&middot;la&acute;dah,</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">and Ha&acute;zar-shu&acute;al and Ba&acute;lah and E&acute;zem,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">and El&middot;to&acute;lad and Be&acute;thul and Hor&acute;mah,</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">and Zik&acute;lag and Beth-mar&acute;ca&middot;both and Ha&acute;zar-su&acute;sah,</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">and Beth-le&middot;ba&acute;oth and Sha&middot;ru&acute;hen; thirteen cities and their settlements.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">A&acute;in, Rim&acute;mon and E&acute;ther and A&acute;shan; four cities and their settlements,</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">and all the settlements that were all around these cities as far as Ba&acute;al&middot;ath-be&acute;er, Ra&acute;mah of the south. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on by their families.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">The inheritance of the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on was out of the allotment of the sons of Judah, because the share of the sons of Judah proved to be too large for them. So the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on got a possession in the midst of their inheritance.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Next the third lot came up for the sons of Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun by their families, and the boundary of their inheritance came to be as far as Sa&acute;rid.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And their boundary went up westward also to Mar&acute;e&middot;al and reached to Dab&acute;be&middot;sheth and reached to the torrent valley that is in front of Jok&acute;ne&middot;am.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And it went back from Sa&acute;rid eastward toward the rising of the sun to the border of Chis&acute;loth-ta&acute;bor and went out to Dab&acute;e&middot;rath and went up to Ja&middot;phi&acute;a.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And from there it passed over eastward toward the sunrise to Gath-he&acute;pher, to Eth-ka&acute;zin, and went out to Rim&acute;mon and was marked out to Ne&acute;ah.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And the boundary went around it on the north to Han&acute;na&middot;thon, and its terminations proved to be at the valley of Iph&acute;tah-el,</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">and Kat&acute;tath and Na&middot;hal&acute;al and Shim&acute;ron and I&acute;da&middot;lah and Beth&acute;le&middot;hem; twelve cities and their settlements.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">This was the inheritance of the sons of Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun by their families. These were the cities and their settlements.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">It was for Is&acute;sa&middot;char that the fourth lot came out, for the sons of Is&acute;sa&middot;char by their families.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And their boundary came to be to Jez&acute;re&middot;el and Che&middot;sul&acute;loth and Shu&acute;nem,</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">and Haph&acute;a&middot;ra&acute;im and Shi&acute;on and An&middot;a&middot;ha&acute;rath,</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">and Rab&acute;bith and Kish&acute;i&middot;on and E&acute;bez,</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">and Re&acute;meth and En-gan&acute;nim and En-had&acute;dah and Beth-paz&acute;zez.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And the boundary reached to Ta&acute;bor and Sha&middot;ha&middot;zu&acute;mah and Beth-she&acute;mesh, and the terminations of their border proved to be at the Jordan; sixteen cities and their settlements.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Is&acute;sa&middot;char by their families, the cities and their settlements.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">Then the fifth lot came out for the tribe of the sons of Ash&acute;er by their families.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And their boundary came to be Hel&acute;kath and Ha&acute;li and Be&acute;ten and Ach&acute;shaph,</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">and Al&middot;lam&acute;me&middot;lech and A&acute;mad and Mi&acute;shal. And it reached westward to Car&acute;mel and to Shi&acute;hor-lib&acute;nath,</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">and it went back toward the rising of the sun to Beth-da&acute;gon and reached to Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun and the valley of Iph&acute;tah-el to the north, to Beth-e&acute;mek and Ne&middot;i&acute;el, and it went out to Ca&acute;bul on the left,</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">and to E&acute;bron and Re&acute;hob and Ham&acute;mon and Ka&acute;nah as far as populous Si&acute;don.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And the boundary went back to Ra&acute;mah and as far as the fortified city of Tyre. And the boundary went back to Ho&acute;sah, and its terminations came to be at the sea in the region of Ach&acute;zib,</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">and Um&acute;mah and A&acute;phek and Re&acute;hob; twenty-two cities and their settlements.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Ash&acute;er by their families. These were the cities and their settlements.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">It was for the sons of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li that the sixth lot came out, for the sons of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li by their families.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And their boundary came to be from He&acute;leph, from the big tree in Za&middot;a&middot;nan&acute;nim, and Ad&acute;a&middot;mi-ne&acute;keb and Jab&acute;ne&middot;el as far as Lak&acute;kum; and its terminations came to be at the Jordan.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">And the boundary went back westward to Az&acute;noth-ta&acute;bor and went out from there to Huk&acute;kok and reached to Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun on the south, and to Ash&acute;er it reached on the west and to Judah at the Jordan toward the rising of the sun.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">And the fortified cities were Zid&acute;dim, Zer and Ham&acute;math, Rak&acute;kath and Chin&acute;ne&middot;reth,</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">and Ad&acute;a&middot;mah and Ra&acute;mah and Ha&acute;zor,</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">and Ke&acute;desh and Ed&acute;re&middot;i and En-ha&acute;zor,</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">and Yi&acute;ron and Mig&acute;dal-el, Ho&acute;rem and Beth-a&acute;nath and Beth-she&acute;mesh; nineteen cities and their settlements.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li by their families, the cities and their settlements.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">It was for the tribe of the sons of Dan by their families that the seventh lot came out.</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">And the border of their inheritance came to be Zo&acute;rah and Esh&acute;ta&middot;ol and Ir-she&acute;mesh,</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">and Sha&middot;al&middot;ab&acute;bin and Ai&acute;ja&middot;lon and Ith&acute;lah,</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">and E&acute;lon and Tim&acute;nah and Ek&acute;ron,</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">and El&acute;te&middot;keh and Gib&acute;be&middot;thon and Ba&acute;al&middot;ath,</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">and Je&acute;hud and Ben&acute;e-be&acute;rak and Gath-rim&acute;mon,</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">and Me-jar&acute;kon and Rak&acute;kon, with the border in front of Jop&acute;pa.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">And the territory of the sons of Dan was too cramped for them. And the sons of Dan proceeded to go up and war against Le&acute;shem and to capture it and strike it with the edge of the sword. Then they took possession of it and went dwelling in it, and they began to call Le&acute;shem Dan, according to the name of Dan their forefather.</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Dan by their families. These were the cities and their settlements.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">Thus they finished dividing the land for a possession by its territories. Then the sons of Israel gave an inheritance to Joshua the son of Nun in their midst.</span> <a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">At the order of Jehovah they gave him the city for which he asked, namely, Tim&acute;nath-se&acute;rah, in the mountainous region of E&acute;phra&middot;im; and he began to build up the city and dwell in it.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">These were the inheritances that El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the sons of Israel distributed as a possession by lot in Shi&acute;loh before Jehovah, at the entrance of the tent of meeting. So they left off from apportioning the land.</span>
</p>
</form>

